H0.text: Humidity is the term that means the amount of water vapor in the air.

H1.text: Temperature is the term that means the amount of water vapor in the air.

H2.text: Pressure is the amount of water vapor in the air.

H3.text: Ambient is the term that refers to the amount of water vapor in the air.

A4.text: Humidity is the concentration of water vapor present in the air.

A5.text: Humidity depends on water vaporization and condensation, which, in turn, mainly depends on temperature.
